\cf2 This is a killer question because your system's ability to do this is genuinely rare. Let me break down where it's money and where it's a trap.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 Where Location Targeting PRINTS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 Tier 1 cities \'97 absolutely yes:\
New York, LA, Chicago, Houston, San Francisco, Seattle, Austin, Miami, Boston, Denver, Atlanta, DC\
Why these work:\
People in these cities have intense local identity. A New Yorker doesn't just live in New York \'97 they ARE a New Yorker. When they hear "you're on the 6 express heading downtown and your chest tightens," that's not a detail \'97 that's a mirror. It triggers the thought "this book was made for me" within the first 30 seconds of the sample. That's the entire conversion battle won.\
Your subtitle strategy is smart: "21 Days After the Breakdown: A Woman's Reset" becomes "21 Days After the Breakdown: A New York Woman's Reset." Google Play indexes that subtitle. Someone searching "self help new york" or "anxiety new york" now finds you. Nobody else is competing for those long-tail keywords because nobody else can produce at this scale.\
Where local cues hit hardest by persona:\
