\cf2 Five titles from one template, one persona. Multiply by 8 personas. That's 40 books from this template alone before you even touch city localization.\
What Makes It Fail\
Two things kill a Morning Weapon book:\
Too preachy. If the Wake-Up Hook sounds like a motivational poster \'97 "Today is a gift! Seize it!" \'97 the listener turns it off and never comes back. The hook has to be honest. Meet them in the dread, the fatigue, the resistance. Then earn the right to offer a shift.\
Too long per chapter. The moment a chapter crosses 8 minutes, you've broken the contract. The promise is "5 minutes." If chapter 6 is suddenly 12 minutes of backstory, the listener feels lied to. Tight, disciplined, every chapter respects their time.\
Want me to go this deep on any of the other templates?\
